canonical:
  title: 賀平安南表
  author: 卞季良
  language: lzh
  text: 帝德廣運覃被萬邦我武惟揚廓淸南極捷音旁達慶頌交騰欽惟勇智邁湯聦明齊舜聲敎冒於出日車書混於普天豈圖小醜之夷久懷姦譎之計始焉誣上而騁詐繼以梗化而干名雖聖人必欲保全每加誨諭乃頑俗莫知改悟益肆跳梁爰致聲罪之誅實爲弔民之擧定戎功於一鼓迅掃妖氛奬忠魂於九泉克申恤典且惠鮮於鰥寡而優禮於賢能喜溢堪輿事光簡冊伏念臣幸逢昭代想聞凱歌迹滯靑丘阻參駿奔之列心馳紫極倍殫虎拜之誠
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 賀平安南表
  author: 卞季良
  language: lzh
  text: 帝德廣運。覃被萬邦。我武惟揚。廓淸南極。捷音旁達。慶頌交騰。欽惟勇智邁湯。聦明齊舜。聲敎冒於出日。車書混於普天。豈圖小醜之夷。久懷姦譎之計。始焉誣上而騁詐。繼以梗化而干名。雖聖人必欲保全。每加誨諭。乃頑俗莫知改悟。益肆跳梁。爰致聲罪之誅。實爲弔民之擧。定戎功於一鼓。迅掃妖氛。奬忠魂於九泉。克申恤典。且惠鮮於鰥寡。而優禮於賢能。喜溢堪輿。事光簡冊。伏念臣幸逢昭代。想聞凱歌。迹滯靑丘。阻參駿奔之列。心馳紫極。倍殫虎拜之誠。
korean:
  title: 하 평안남 표
  author: 변계량
  language: kor
  text: 제덕(帝德)이 널리 운행되어 늘이어 만방(萬邦)에 미치고, 내 무력(武力)을 드날려 남극(南極)을 확청(廓淸)하시니, 첩보(捷報)가 사방에 들리자 경축이 번갈아 솟아오르나이다. 공경히 생각하옵건대, 용지(勇智)는 탕(湯) 임금보다 더하시고 총명이 순(舜) 임금과 같으시어, 성교(聲敎)가 해뜨는 고장에까지 미치고, 수레의 궤도와 문자가 하늘 아래 모두 통일되었사온데, 뜻밖에도 추악한 조그만 오랑캐가 오래 간사한 계교를 품어, 처음엔 위를 속여 사기(詐欺)를 일삼다가 끝내는 왕화(王化)를 가로막고 신사(臣事)를 거절하여, 비록 성인(聖人)이 반드시 보전하려고 번번이 회유(誨諭)를 더하여도 저 완악한 무리들이 개오(改悟)할 줄을 몰라 더욱 방자하게 도량(跳梁)하므로, 이에 죄를 성토하는 주륙(誅戮)을 행하였사오나, 실은 백성을 위로하는 의거(義擧)였나이다. 한번 북[鼔]을 쳐 무공(武功)을 정(定)하여 요망한 기운을 홱 쓸어버리시고, 구천(九泉)에 충혼(忠魂)들을 위로하고 장려하시어 곧 휼전(恤典)을 베푸시며, 또 홀아비와 과부들에게 구호의 은전을 내리시고, 어질고 유능한 자를 예(禮)로 우대하시니, 기쁨이 온 세계에 넘치고 일이 역사책에 빛나옵나이다. 엎드려 생각하옵건대, 신(臣)이 다행히 소대(昭代)를 만나 개가(凱歌)를 상상하며 듣자옵고, 몸이 청구(靑丘)에 매어 준분(駿奔)의 열(列)에 참가하지 못하오나, 마음은 자극(紫極)으로 달려 곱절로 호배(虎拜)의 정성을 다하옵나이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0350_010_0610&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Memorial on the Subjugation of Annam
  author: Byeon Gyeryang
  language: eng
  text: Your Majesty's virtue extends broadly, its influence reaching all lands. Our military prowess shines forth, sweeping clear the Southern reaches. News of victory spreads in all directions, and celebrations rise in waves of joy. We humbly reflect that your courage and wisdom surpass even the sage-king Tang, your clarity rivals the enlightenment of Shun. Your teachings reach lands where the sun rises, and the tracks of your chariots and the script of your words unify all under heaven. Yet unexpectedly, these base savages harbored treacherous schemes for ages, first deceiving their superiors and practicing deceit, then obstructing the transforming influence of virtue and rejecting their duty as subjects. Though the Sage repeatedly offered them counsel and reformation, these stubborn people refused to awaken and grew ever more audacious in their rebellion. Thus we executed the punishment their crimes deserved—yet this was truly an act of compassion for the people. With one beat of the drum, your martial achievement was secured, sweeping away the noxious vapors in an instant. You honored the loyal spirits in the nine springs below, extending your grace to them, and bestowed upon the widows and orphans the comfort of imperial care, while elevating the virtuous and capable with proper respect. Joy overflows throughout all creation, and this deed shines immortal in the pages of history. Your humble servant, fortunate to live in this enlightened age, imagines hearing songs of your triumph, yet my body remains bound to this Eastern land, unable to join the ranks of those who rush to serve you. But my heart races toward the Purple Palace, and with doubled sincerity I offer the deepest obeisance of a loyal subject.
  footnotes:
    - Tang and Shun are legendary sage-kings of ancient China, representing the highest ideals of virtuous rulership.
    - The 'nine springs below' (九泉) is a poetic reference to the underworld or the realm of the deceased.
    - The 'Purple Palace' (紫極) refers to the imperial court or the emperor's residence.
    - This is a memorial (表) formally presented to praise the emperor's military victory over Annam and his virtuous governance.
    - The 'Eastern land' (靑丘) refers to Korea itself, from which the author writes.
